
-- To copy or replicate all stored procedures from one database to another in SQL Server 2016 and newer, here are your best options — both manual and automated:
-- ask AI: sql server how to copy or replicate all stored procedures from one database to another?

--✅ Option 1: Generate Scripts with SSMS
Open SQL Server Management Studio (SSMS).

Right-click the source database > Tasks > Generate Scripts.

Choose "Select specific database objects".

Check Stored Procedures only.

Click Next, then choose:

"Save to file" or "New Query Window".

Click Advanced and set:

"Script USE DATABASE" = False

"Script DROP and CREATE" = Create only (or Drop and Create if needed)

Execute the script on the target database.
